1
00:01:06,336 --> 00:01:10,778
=The Truth=

2
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,136
=Episode 22=

3
00:01:20,893 --> 00:01:22,093
You look so handsome.

4
00:01:23,212 --> 00:01:24,412
You dance so well.

5
00:01:26,093 --> 00:01:26,733
Come dance.

6
00:01:36,453 --> 00:01:37,572
What the heck?

7
00:01:37,572 --> 00:01:38,932
What did he send?

8
00:01:43,013 --> 00:01:44,533
We're all set on our end, right?

9
00:01:52,253 --> 00:01:53,373
After all this buildup,

10
00:01:54,212 --> 00:01:55,613
it's time to settle this.

11
00:02:42,692 --> 00:02:43,813
Little Qian.

12
00:02:45,732 --> 00:02:48,933
It's me, Si Yuanlong.
Little Qian, open up.

13
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:53,692
I'm miserable.

14
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:58,892
I feel like I got dumped.

15
00:02:59,773 --> 00:03:02,053
Were you even in a relationship
to get dumped?

16
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:03,973
Why'd you have to bring that up?

17
00:03:03,973 --> 00:03:05,732
Can't you at least try to comfort me?

18
00:03:10,373 --> 00:03:11,533
I'm heading to bed first.

19
00:03:13,572 --> 00:03:16,493
If you cook me instant noodles,
I'll feel much better.

20
00:03:17,012 --> 00:03:18,213
Do I look that idle?

21
00:03:18,213 --> 00:03:20,292
You came at midnight
and expect me to cook for you?

22
00:03:21,373 --> 00:03:22,732
But you moved out of the dorm.

23
00:03:22,732 --> 00:03:24,253
Where else could I find you?

24
00:03:24,253 --> 00:03:25,973
How about I order delivery instead?

25
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:28,653
We'll get some food and drinks and chat.

26
00:03:45,213 --> 00:03:47,053
Are you cooking it or throwing it away?

27
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:48,056
Throwing it away.

28
00:03:49,253 --> 00:03:49,973
Cooking it.

29
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:02,292
Your beef patties
are so meaty and flavorful.

30
00:04:02,572 --> 00:04:03,572
Give me another one.

31
00:04:07,612 --> 00:04:09,493
I'm a guest here.
Heat up another one for me.

32
00:04:09,852 --> 00:04:11,053
I have to do it myself?

33
00:04:14,053 --> 00:04:15,612
Who are you packing that for?

34
00:04:16,492 --> 00:04:18,492
Just eat. Stop being nosy.

35
00:04:27,653 --> 00:04:28,732
I have to do it myself.

36
00:04:41,013 --> 00:04:41,812
Morning, Master.

37
00:04:42,732 --> 00:04:43,653
Morning.

38
00:05:08,052 --> 00:05:08,893
Bribing me?

39
00:05:10,812 --> 00:05:11,612
Suppose so.

40
00:05:12,492 --> 00:05:13,172
What's up?

41
00:05:13,653 --> 00:05:15,852
I want to take a few days off
after the case wraps up.

42
00:05:17,732 --> 00:05:18,612
Absolutely not.

43
00:05:19,013 --> 00:05:19,973
We'll discuss it later.

44
00:05:43,252 --> 00:05:43,893
Dad.

45
00:05:45,492 --> 00:05:46,252
Why are you here?

46
00:05:46,453 --> 00:05:47,333
Mom's downstairs.

47
00:05:47,732 --> 00:05:48,693
Bring her up then.

48
00:05:51,292 --> 00:05:51,932
Hello?

49
00:05:52,932 --> 00:05:54,932
I'm here on a one-day business trip.

50
00:05:54,932 --> 00:05:55,973
I'm heading back tonight.

51
00:05:56,412 --> 00:05:58,333
Xiaoyu insisted on coming to your place.

52
00:05:58,333 --> 00:05:59,573
He said your place is fun.

53
00:06:00,172 --> 00:06:01,653
Okay, got it.

54
00:06:02,732 --> 00:06:04,292
Stay safe out there.

55
00:06:04,653 --> 00:06:05,573
Sorry for the trouble.

56
00:06:06,412 --> 00:06:08,653
Don't talk nonsense. Okay.

57
00:06:13,252 --> 00:06:15,292
What did you tell your mom?

58
00:06:16,213 --> 00:06:17,812
Said it's fun here?

59
00:06:18,292 --> 00:06:19,292
Know what this place is?

60
00:06:20,093 --> 00:06:21,812
This is where we solve crimes,
understand?

61
00:06:22,492 --> 00:06:23,893
No more nonsense from now on.

62
00:06:25,533 --> 00:06:26,252
Do you hear me?

63
00:06:27,252 --> 00:06:29,412
Don't mention my gaming to my mom.

64
00:06:29,412 --> 00:06:31,052
She nags me just for being on my phone.

65
00:06:31,612 --> 00:06:33,213
You and your little tricks.

66
00:06:33,453 --> 00:06:35,653
You know I won't stop you
from gaming, huh?

67
00:06:36,292 --> 00:06:37,573
Cut down on gaming.

68
00:06:37,812 --> 00:06:39,852
Read more books. Got it?

69
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:41,653
It's not good for your health.

70
00:06:41,653 --> 00:06:43,653
Look how you're slouching again.

71
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:47,093
Any plan for later?

72
00:06:47,693 --> 00:06:48,533
Not going anywhere.

73
00:06:48,893 --> 00:06:50,333
What do you mean by that?

74
00:06:51,573 --> 00:06:52,412
Got work to do.

75
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:53,172
What kind of work?

76
00:06:53,693 --> 00:06:54,904
Knowing parents' occupations.

77
00:06:57,013 --> 00:06:58,213
I knew it.

78
00:07:47,292 --> 00:07:47,932
Wang Tong,

79
00:07:48,453 --> 00:07:49,453
go get Zhang for me.

80
00:07:49,453 --> 00:07:49,973
Okay.

81
00:07:54,052 --> 00:07:54,732
Lei.

82
00:08:35,173 --> 00:08:35,892
Well?

83
00:08:36,492 --> 00:08:37,173
Chief Xu.

84
00:08:37,772 --> 00:08:38,532
Captain Leng.

85
00:08:40,012 --> 00:08:42,453
So far we've found three fetal remains.

86
00:08:43,372 --> 00:08:45,532
These fetuses have fully formed faces

87
00:08:46,732 --> 00:08:47,772
with eyelids open

88
00:08:48,453 --> 00:08:49,693
and limbs fully developed.

89
00:08:50,053 --> 00:08:51,573
They measure about 26 cm in length

90
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:53,532
and weigh about 1.5 kg.

91
00:08:53,892 --> 00:08:56,693
They were likely
over 28 weeks gestational age.

92
00:08:57,173 --> 00:08:59,652
Judging by tissue fluid evaporation
on the surface,

93
00:08:59,813 --> 00:09:02,053
they were extracted
from the womb recently.

94
00:09:02,933 --> 00:09:04,173
At most two or three days ago.

95
00:09:04,933 --> 00:09:06,053
At this late stage,

96
00:09:06,053 --> 00:09:07,093
likely induced abortions.

97
00:09:07,933 --> 00:09:09,372
All fetuses show abnormalities.

98
00:09:09,852 --> 00:09:11,093
Brain development deformities.

99
00:09:12,053 --> 00:09:12,852
A back-alley clinic?

100
00:09:13,293 --> 00:09:14,093
Possibly.

101
00:09:14,612 --> 00:09:16,532
I've collected tissue samples
from the fetuses.

102
00:09:16,532 --> 00:09:19,093
I'll arrange for lab tests immediately
after returning

103
00:09:19,453 --> 00:09:22,252
to see if we can find the donors
of their sex chromosomes.

104
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:31,333
With such a public setting

105
00:09:31,453 --> 00:09:32,252
and so many people,

106
00:09:32,252 --> 00:09:33,492
the suspect was being bold.

107
00:09:35,173 --> 00:09:36,213
Judging by the situation,

108
00:09:36,213 --> 00:09:39,213
I suspect the news is already spreading
like wildfire online.

109
00:09:41,453 --> 00:09:42,933
Hello, Chief.

110
00:09:46,732 --> 00:09:47,453
Yes.

111
00:09:48,813 --> 00:09:49,492
Understood.

112
00:09:52,053 --> 00:09:54,453
The higher-ups are aware of this matter.

113
00:09:55,693 --> 00:09:56,333
Here's the plan.

114
00:09:56,892 --> 00:09:57,772
Categorize it first.

115
00:09:58,173 --> 00:09:59,132
And be meticulous.

116
00:09:59,973 --> 00:10:03,372
Nowadays,
anyone can spout nonsense online.

117
00:10:03,693 --> 00:10:05,293
Who knows what stories they'll make up?

118
00:10:26,372 --> 00:10:30,093
Surveillance shows
the body dumper is a male

119
00:10:30,093 --> 00:10:31,173
around 30 years old.

120
00:10:31,813 --> 00:10:33,532
He appears tall,

121
00:10:34,132 --> 00:10:35,293
roughly 190 cm.

122
00:10:35,372 --> 00:10:36,612
He has a slight out-toed gait.

123
00:10:37,252 --> 00:10:40,053
Then he got in a taxi.

124
00:10:44,732 --> 00:10:47,772
We've contacted the taxi company.

125
00:10:48,213 --> 00:10:49,732
According to the driver,

126
00:10:50,732 --> 00:10:51,732
he had a northern accent.

127
00:10:52,372 --> 00:10:55,652
He was dropped off north
of Guoqing East Road subway station.

128
00:10:55,772 --> 00:10:57,173
Then he was off the grid.

129
00:11:02,252 --> 00:11:03,732
The DNA from the three fetuses

130
00:11:03,732 --> 00:11:05,772
comes from three distinct sets
of parents.

131
00:11:06,652 --> 00:11:08,492
Judging by fetal development,

132
00:11:08,612 --> 00:11:10,573
the fertilization times
were likely very close.

133
00:11:10,933 --> 00:11:13,333
Women's ovulation periods
vary individually.

134
00:11:13,652 --> 00:11:15,652
Achieving such precise timing

135
00:11:16,173 --> 00:11:18,813
suggests usage
of ovulation-inducing drugs

136
00:11:19,093 --> 00:11:21,093
and artificial insemination.

137
00:11:22,693 --> 00:11:23,892
Illegal surrogacy?

138
00:11:24,093 --> 00:11:24,693
Right.

139
00:11:25,173 --> 00:11:28,532
Also, we extracted methamphetamine
from the fetuses' organs and blood.

140
00:11:30,293 --> 00:11:31,093
Meth?

141
00:11:36,532 --> 00:11:39,093
(No match)
Fingerprints are detected

142
00:11:39,093 --> 00:11:40,132
on the plastic wrapping.

143
00:11:40,132 --> 00:11:41,053
After comparison,

144
00:11:41,852 --> 00:11:43,573
identity information remains unknown.

145
00:11:47,053 --> 00:11:50,732
Meth causes
fetal brain development deformities.

146
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:55,573
The three surrogates
are either long-term drug users

147
00:11:56,252 --> 00:11:59,772
or ingested large quantities of drugs
within a short timeframe.

148
00:12:00,852 --> 00:12:01,933
That doesn't make sense.

149
00:12:01,933 --> 00:12:05,813
Who'd hire drug users as surrogates?

150
00:12:08,173 --> 00:12:10,732
I checked long-term drug user records
in the system

151
00:12:11,213 --> 00:12:13,693
and found a DNA match
for one maternal source.

152
00:12:13,693 --> 00:12:14,453
(Wu Cuimiao's Info)

153
00:12:14,453 --> 00:12:15,892
Wu Cuimiao, female,

154
00:12:16,612 --> 00:12:17,573
26 years old,

155
00:12:17,732 --> 00:12:18,573
from Qianzhou.

156
00:12:18,732 --> 00:12:21,772
She has been repeatedly penalized
for prostitution and drug use.

157
00:12:30,492 --> 00:12:31,293
Master.

158
00:12:48,333 --> 00:12:49,053
Ye Qian.

159
00:12:52,652 --> 00:12:53,413
Thank you, Master.

160
00:12:53,413 --> 00:12:54,213
Be careful.

161
00:12:54,813 --> 00:12:55,612
Rest assured.

162
00:13:52,252 --> 00:13:52,813
Boss.

163
00:14:01,693 --> 00:14:02,413
Boss.

164
00:14:06,573 --> 00:14:07,492
Don't worry, boss.

165
00:14:07,612 --> 00:14:08,892
We've swept the entire area.

166
00:14:08,892 --> 00:14:09,693
All clear.

167
00:15:25,852 --> 00:15:26,652
We're here.

168
00:15:32,772 --> 00:15:33,453
After you.

169
00:15:48,132 --> 00:15:49,132
Nice place.

170
00:15:49,813 --> 00:15:51,372
Thanks to Officer Ye's arrangements.

171
00:15:58,012 --> 00:16:00,293
Are you planning to cook on-site?

172
00:16:00,852 --> 00:16:03,413
Can you guarantee quality?

173
00:16:03,532 --> 00:16:04,652
Don't worry, Mr. Bao.

174
00:16:05,053 --> 00:16:09,573
All southwest products
previously passed through my hands.

175
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:11,093
Terrific.

176
00:16:12,573 --> 00:16:13,372
Can't wait.

177
00:16:17,093 --> 00:16:20,372
You need to add another two percent
to the agreed price.

178
00:16:21,012 --> 00:16:21,852
Two percent?

179
00:16:25,012 --> 00:16:25,813
Mr. Zhang,

180
00:16:26,612 --> 00:16:28,933
Monkey's now on police radar.

181
00:16:29,813 --> 00:16:32,732
Without his insurance,
he won't dare flip easily.

182
00:16:33,532 --> 00:16:35,252
It makes him much easier
for you to control.

183
00:16:36,492 --> 00:16:37,453
So

184
00:16:46,213 --> 00:16:47,173
I want ten percent.

185
00:16:47,933 --> 00:16:48,772
What do you think?

186
00:17:11,453 --> 00:17:12,893
Twenty percent works too.

187
00:17:16,252 --> 00:17:17,893
Meeting you, Officer Ye,

188
00:17:18,373 --> 00:17:19,173
is worth it.

189
00:17:20,133 --> 00:17:21,973
Let's communicate and exchange more.

190
00:17:22,853 --> 00:17:24,012
It depends on your actions.

191
00:18:07,532 --> 00:18:09,973
I haven't been called Mr. Zhang in ages.

192
00:18:12,732 --> 00:18:14,893
I'm not used
to these underworld nicknames.

193
00:18:15,532 --> 00:18:16,453
You don't mind, do you?

194
00:18:18,613 --> 00:18:21,092
I know what caliber
you operate at, Officer Ye.

195
00:18:24,973 --> 00:18:27,092
Mixing with Huo's gang

196
00:18:27,092 --> 00:18:30,052
is somewhat beneath your talents.

197
00:18:30,572 --> 00:18:32,532
Is that how you view your partners?

198
00:18:35,613 --> 00:18:37,732
It's the synthetic drug era.

199
00:18:37,772 --> 00:18:39,492
It was never their forte anyway.

200
00:18:41,052 --> 00:18:42,052
If the price suits,

201
00:18:42,052 --> 00:18:43,256
we can replace them anytime.

202
00:18:47,613 --> 00:18:52,252
What matters are the resources
and channels you provide.

203
00:18:53,092 --> 00:18:54,532
This is the most valuable thing.

204
00:18:54,532 --> 00:18:55,252
I know.

205
00:18:56,853 --> 00:18:57,853
So blunt?

206
00:18:58,613 --> 00:19:00,332
Not afraid I'll jack up the price again?

207
00:19:06,092 --> 00:19:06,853
No.

208
00:19:09,012 --> 00:19:10,973
It shows you really want
to do business with me.

209
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:34,693
(Yunxi Police)

210
00:19:34,693 --> 00:19:36,373
Alright, you look good enough.

211
00:19:38,213 --> 00:19:40,052
Stop preening and put it away.

212
00:19:42,693 --> 00:19:43,893
So you're Wu Cuimiao?

213
00:19:44,252 --> 00:19:45,812
Do you know why we called you in?

214
00:19:46,012 --> 00:19:46,853
No.

215
00:19:47,893 --> 00:19:49,853
You're a regular at the police station.

216
00:19:50,012 --> 00:19:51,092
Any idea why?

217
00:19:51,373 --> 00:19:52,252
You know what?

218
00:19:52,772 --> 00:19:55,532
This is actually my first time
at the city police department.

219
00:19:55,693 --> 00:19:56,693
Watch your attitude.

220
00:19:59,853 --> 00:20:00,973
Put it away. Hurry.

221
00:20:01,492 --> 00:20:02,252
Fine.

222
00:20:02,572 --> 00:20:04,332
Cooperate? Sure, I will.

223
00:20:05,812 --> 00:20:08,693
I haven't done anything wrong lately.

224
00:20:08,772 --> 00:20:10,492
I've been staying home, behaving myself.

225
00:20:11,012 --> 00:20:12,052
Listen to me.

226
00:20:12,252 --> 00:20:14,693
Surrogacy is illegal in our country.

227
00:20:14,973 --> 00:20:17,732
All the income you received is illegal.

228
00:20:18,173 --> 00:20:18,893
Wait.

229
00:20:20,732 --> 00:20:23,532
You're not going
to take it all back, are you?

230
00:20:24,613 --> 00:20:25,893
There really wasn't much.

231
00:20:26,133 --> 00:20:28,173
They haven't even paid
the final installment yet.

232
00:20:28,292 --> 00:20:30,373
Oh my god, what a loss.

233
00:20:31,693 --> 00:20:32,973
Why didn't they pay it?

234
00:20:33,252 --> 00:20:34,933
They said the baby was deformed,

235
00:20:35,173 --> 00:20:36,173
so they couldn't keep it.

236
00:20:37,252 --> 00:20:38,693
Just decided not to take it.

237
00:20:39,133 --> 00:20:40,532
How heartless is that?

238
00:20:42,693 --> 00:20:45,213
I didn't mean to.

239
00:20:45,772 --> 00:20:47,052
Just couldn't resist.

240
00:20:47,613 --> 00:20:50,693
Tell us everything about your surrogacy.

241
00:20:51,332 --> 00:20:52,572
This job

242
00:20:53,012 --> 00:20:56,413
was introduced by a girl I met
when I sold my eggs before.

243
00:20:56,572 --> 00:20:58,732
I was a bit short on cash at the time.

244
00:20:59,572 --> 00:21:00,453
What agency?

245
00:21:00,492 --> 00:21:01,453
Where was it located?

246
00:21:02,653 --> 00:21:04,492
I really don't know its name.

247
00:21:04,933 --> 00:21:07,052
Anyway, after I agreed,

248
00:21:07,092 --> 00:21:08,613
someone contacted me.

249
00:21:10,133 --> 00:21:12,252
It was at a private clinic in a resort

250
00:21:12,252 --> 00:21:13,332
in the western suburbs.

251
00:21:13,532 --> 00:21:14,492
What resort?

252
00:21:16,572 --> 00:21:19,092
I really forgot what it was called.

253
00:21:21,532 --> 00:21:23,133
There was an archway at the main gate.

254
00:21:23,973 --> 00:21:25,572
Then where did you get the drugs?

255
00:21:28,252 --> 00:21:29,133
What?

256
00:21:30,812 --> 00:21:32,133
Playing dumb again?

257
00:21:33,772 --> 00:21:34,893
Answer the question.

258
00:21:37,092 --> 00:21:38,572
After the embryo transfer was done,

259
00:21:39,173 --> 00:21:42,373
they arranged for us all
to stay at the resort.

260
00:21:42,373 --> 00:21:44,213
Nothing to do all day.

261
00:21:44,213 --> 00:21:45,653
Just eating and drinking.

262
00:21:45,973 --> 00:21:46,853
Could go online,

263
00:21:46,853 --> 00:21:47,973
but weren't allowed to go.

264
00:21:48,332 --> 00:21:50,252
It was so boring.

265
00:21:50,933 --> 00:21:53,173
Liu, who looked after us,
got us some stuff.

266
00:21:53,732 --> 00:21:54,693
What about the others?

267
00:21:55,693 --> 00:21:56,653
What others?

268
00:21:56,653 --> 00:21:59,453
The other two whose pregnancies
were terminated for the same reason.

269
00:21:59,893 --> 00:22:00,772
Listen to me.

270
00:22:01,052 --> 00:22:03,292
If you were the one
who provided them with the drugs...

271
00:22:03,292 --> 00:22:04,052
No, no, no.

272
00:22:04,693 --> 00:22:06,373
Theirs had nothing to do with me.

273
00:22:06,653 --> 00:22:08,092
Liu gave it to them.

274
00:22:08,732 --> 00:22:10,332
Liu? His full name.

275
00:22:11,572 --> 00:22:12,373
Liu Yong.

276
00:22:17,693 --> 00:22:18,492
Is this him?

277
00:22:20,332 --> 00:22:21,572
His address and number.

278
00:22:23,973 --> 00:22:25,933
He was just the driver

279
00:22:25,933 --> 00:22:28,012
and looked after our daily needs.

280
00:22:28,012 --> 00:22:29,732
He stayed with us at the resort.

281
00:22:30,052 --> 00:22:31,532
Nobody calls nowadays.

282
00:22:33,572 --> 00:22:34,732
He does have WeChat.

283
00:22:39,173 --> 00:22:39,893
What?

284
00:22:39,893 --> 00:22:40,693
WeChat.

285
00:22:42,772 --> 00:22:43,572
WeChat.

286
00:22:49,213 --> 00:22:52,052
Egg retrieval and surrogacy
are both quite risky.

287
00:22:52,572 --> 00:22:54,332
You're pretty bold.

288
00:22:54,332 --> 00:22:55,693
Not afraid something might happen?

289
00:22:57,453 --> 00:22:59,052
Lots of people do this.

290
00:22:59,052 --> 00:22:59,853
What's the big deal?

291
00:23:00,213 --> 00:23:01,693
Haven't seen anyone get into trouble.

292
00:23:02,893 --> 00:23:04,373
Arrange a urine test for her.

293
00:23:04,492 --> 00:23:05,173
Yes.

294
00:23:05,173 --> 00:23:07,092
Wait, that's unnecessary.

295
00:23:07,252 --> 00:23:08,373
Come on, bro.

296
00:23:08,572 --> 00:23:09,572
What 'bro'?

297
00:23:09,572 --> 00:23:11,092
You had your chance to confess.

298
00:23:11,092 --> 00:23:12,453
Leniency for confession.

299
00:23:12,453 --> 00:23:13,973
You've been resisting the whole time.

300
00:23:13,973 --> 00:23:16,173
I... I did say it.

301
00:23:16,252 --> 00:23:17,012
Say what?

302
00:23:17,012 --> 00:23:18,252
None of it made any sense.

303
00:23:18,252 --> 00:23:18,772
Do the test.

304
00:23:18,772 --> 00:23:20,292
I've said everything I need to.

305
00:23:20,413 --> 00:23:21,413
Enough. Sit down.

306
00:23:34,296 --> 00:23:36,120
(Yunxi Western International
Tourism Resort)

307
00:23:41,976 --> 00:23:48,566
(West Suburb People's Clinic)

308
00:23:56,052 --> 00:23:56,693
Captain Leng,

309
00:23:57,208 --> 00:23:59,332
this is the person
in charge of this private clinic.

310
00:23:59,332 --> 00:24:01,413
He's admitted
to running the surrogacy business.

311
00:24:01,413 --> 00:24:02,572
Still haven't found Liu Yong.

312
00:24:03,373 --> 00:24:04,772
Is Liu Yong your employee?

313
00:24:06,413 --> 00:24:07,532
I've always treated

314
00:24:08,092 --> 00:24:09,252
Liu Yong well.

315
00:24:09,332 --> 00:24:10,572
And he stabs me in the back?

316
00:24:10,933 --> 00:24:12,613
I've been in this business for years.

317
00:24:12,772 --> 00:24:13,812
My success rate is high.

318
00:24:14,492 --> 00:24:16,213
No client has ever been dissatisfied.

319
00:24:16,373 --> 00:24:18,133
My good reputation
is ruined because of him.

320
00:24:18,693 --> 00:24:22,092
You do know surrogacy is illegal, right?

321
00:24:24,213 --> 00:24:26,173
Tell us in detail about Liu Yong.

322
00:24:26,853 --> 00:24:30,012
He's just a distant relative of mine.

323
00:24:30,092 --> 00:24:32,133
No education, no decent skills.

324
00:24:32,373 --> 00:24:33,693
If he weren't family,

325
00:24:33,693 --> 00:24:34,893
I wouldn't have hired him.

326
00:24:36,332 --> 00:24:37,292
Now,

327
00:24:38,653 --> 00:24:40,292
besides being a driver,

328
00:24:40,413 --> 00:24:43,292
he just does odd jobs and errands.

329
00:24:43,973 --> 00:24:45,292
An ungrateful wolf.

330
00:24:46,613 --> 00:24:48,173
Does Liu Yong do drugs?

331
00:24:48,933 --> 00:24:49,572
He...

332
00:24:49,973 --> 00:24:52,893
H-He used to... used to...

333
00:24:52,893 --> 00:24:55,413
But now... now he says
he quit a long time ago.

334
00:24:55,893 --> 00:24:57,492
No, not anymore.

335
00:25:01,613 --> 00:25:02,332
Liu Yong!

336
00:25:03,413 --> 00:25:04,252
Stop right there!

337
00:25:21,052 --> 00:25:21,853
Keep running.

338
00:25:28,572 --> 00:25:29,413
Why did you run?

339
00:25:30,492 --> 00:25:31,772
Scared now?

340
00:25:32,653 --> 00:25:34,292
Why did you give drugs
to pregnant women?

341
00:25:35,812 --> 00:25:37,012
I admit to doing meth.

342
00:25:37,332 --> 00:25:40,653
But I didn't give it to those women.
It was Wu Cuimiao.

343
00:25:41,133 --> 00:25:43,532
Once she caught me sneaking a hit.

344
00:25:43,853 --> 00:25:44,933
She asked me for some.

345
00:25:45,173 --> 00:25:46,213
So you gave it to her?

346
00:25:46,213 --> 00:25:47,252
Of course I didn't.

347
00:25:47,252 --> 00:25:48,373
I paid for it myself.

348
00:25:48,373 --> 00:25:49,572
Why should I give it to her?

349
00:25:50,292 --> 00:25:52,732
Besides, she was pregnant.

350
00:25:52,893 --> 00:25:54,613
I'm not that much of a scumbag.

351
00:25:54,893 --> 00:25:56,373
She pestered me several times.

352
00:25:56,453 --> 00:25:57,532
I ignored her.

353
00:25:57,933 --> 00:25:59,572
Then when I was out
working for the boss,

354
00:25:59,572 --> 00:26:01,693
she went into my room
and took my entire stash.

355
00:26:02,492 --> 00:26:05,012
I only found out
when I went looking for her.

356
00:26:07,973 --> 00:26:09,332
Why did you go to City Square?

357
00:26:13,453 --> 00:26:16,332
Because of that matter,
my boss said he'd fire me,

358
00:26:16,332 --> 00:26:18,252
and all the losses
would be pinned on me.

359
00:26:18,252 --> 00:26:19,292
This is not fair.

360
00:26:19,613 --> 00:26:21,292
He never treated me well anyway.

361
00:26:21,613 --> 00:26:22,973
He makes so much money

362
00:26:22,973 --> 00:26:24,413
and pays me peanuts.

363
00:26:24,413 --> 00:26:25,973
And he always orders me around.

364
00:26:26,613 --> 00:26:29,572
I got mad and thought
I'd just blow the whole thing wide open.

365
00:26:30,052 --> 00:26:31,933
His money isn't clean anyway.

366
00:26:31,973 --> 00:26:33,292
I'd expose him to the light.

367
00:26:37,812 --> 00:26:42,532
Did you tell Liu Yong
to dispose of the fetuses?

368
00:26:45,492 --> 00:26:46,613
I arranged abortions

369
00:26:46,613 --> 00:26:48,292
as soon as I realized
something was wrong.

370
00:26:48,732 --> 00:26:49,973
Three of them.

371
00:26:50,292 --> 00:26:52,772
A whole year's profit
won't cover the compensation.

372
00:26:53,173 --> 00:26:55,332
Afterwards, I even asked him
if he'd given them drugs.

373
00:26:55,332 --> 00:26:56,812
He wouldn't admit it.

374
00:26:56,812 --> 00:26:59,732
I told him to find a deserted place
to bury them.

375
00:26:59,732 --> 00:27:00,613
And what did he do?

376
00:27:00,973 --> 00:27:02,732
This is pure retaliation.

377
00:27:03,572 --> 00:27:05,213
Why would Liu Yong
retaliate against you?

378
00:27:05,492 --> 00:27:07,173
He thinks he's underpaid and overworked.

379
00:27:08,133 --> 00:27:09,933
He never considers his own worth.

380
00:27:12,133 --> 00:27:15,373
Also, I might have scolded him that day

381
00:27:15,373 --> 00:27:17,012
and... and hit him.

382
00:27:19,052 --> 00:27:21,092
Coward, won't own up to what he did.

383
00:27:21,772 --> 00:27:22,613
Regret it?

384
00:27:24,052 --> 00:27:26,853
You should regret running
an illegal business, understand?

385
00:27:27,973 --> 00:27:28,613
Understand?

386
00:27:33,812 --> 00:27:36,893
We learned from several surrogates

387
00:27:37,853 --> 00:27:40,133
that you stole Liu Yong's drugs, right?

388
00:27:41,453 --> 00:27:45,292
And you encouraged them to take drugs,

389
00:27:45,373 --> 00:27:47,092
claiming it would excite
and energize them.

390
00:27:48,252 --> 00:27:49,492
Why did you do that?

391
00:27:51,613 --> 00:27:52,772
For fun.

392
00:27:54,812 --> 00:27:56,133
You know what they say?

393
00:27:57,332 --> 00:28:00,572
Having fun alone is boring anyway.

394
00:28:00,653 --> 00:28:02,373
Might as well have fun together.

395
00:28:03,653 --> 00:28:05,933
Do you realize the nature of that?

396
00:28:07,012 --> 00:28:07,973
Being helpful?

397
00:28:10,332 --> 00:28:11,413
What is this attitude?

398
00:28:11,973 --> 00:28:13,373
Fix your attitude.

399
00:28:13,532 --> 00:28:14,732
You broke the law.

400
00:28:14,732 --> 00:28:16,012
It's a crime, understand?

401
00:28:16,012 --> 00:28:17,613
But nothing happened, did it?

402
00:28:19,252 --> 00:28:22,292
Besides, why blame only me?

403
00:28:23,012 --> 00:28:25,532
It's their own fault
for being ignorant and weak-willed.

404
00:28:26,252 --> 00:28:30,292
You're endangering yourself and others
with this attitude and lifestyle.

405
00:28:30,292 --> 00:28:31,213
Do you understand?

406
00:28:34,693 --> 00:28:36,373
I take it one day at a time.

407
00:28:37,292 --> 00:28:38,532
That's just how I like to live.

408
00:28:38,772 --> 00:28:40,012
It's none of your business.

409
00:28:44,728 --> 00:28:46,973
(No-Name Diner)

410
00:28:46,973 --> 00:28:47,653
Qiming,

411
00:28:48,092 --> 00:28:50,532
the Narcotics Division acted
on Liu Yong's confession

412
00:28:50,532 --> 00:28:52,812
and located his drug supplier.

413
00:28:54,133 --> 00:28:55,052
After verification,

414
00:28:55,772 --> 00:28:58,213
that person is a key figure
in Bao Hei's gang.

415
00:28:58,693 --> 00:29:01,812
Since Liu Yong and he
were former drug buddies,

416
00:29:02,532 --> 00:29:05,492
he didn't stay guarded around Liu Yong.

417
00:29:05,653 --> 00:29:06,653
Moreover,

418
00:29:06,653 --> 00:29:09,693
the Narcotics Division
couldn't identify him previously.

419
00:29:09,693 --> 00:29:13,732
Unexpectedly, our case
uncovered his background.

420
00:29:13,893 --> 00:29:16,613
With the key clues from our case,

421
00:29:16,853 --> 00:29:20,572
dismantling Bao Hei's gang
can happen sooner.

422
00:29:20,572 --> 00:29:21,173
That's good.

423
00:29:21,653 --> 00:29:23,012
Alright, go eat.

424
00:29:56,772 --> 00:29:57,933
Guess what he said?

425
00:29:59,413 --> 00:30:00,812
I can guess some of it.

426
00:30:02,613 --> 00:30:03,693
What are our plans next?

427
00:30:04,492 --> 00:30:05,453
Deliver the goods first

428
00:30:05,772 --> 00:30:06,893
and get the money.

429
00:30:08,693 --> 00:30:10,252
How long will the delivery take?

430
00:30:10,453 --> 00:30:11,252
When it's time...

431
00:30:11,453 --> 00:30:12,732
Don't worry about the details.

432
00:30:13,292 --> 00:30:14,853
I'll notify you when it's nearly done.

433
00:30:32,343 --> 00:30:34,424
(Dan Qing)

434
00:30:34,424 --> 00:30:40,008
♪After all, we've grown up
a bit these past few years♪

435
00:30:41,531 --> 00:30:47,283
♪Looking back at old times,
there's a touch of sweetness♪

436
00:30:48,504 --> 00:30:55,089
♪If time could flow backwards,
could the past be revisited♪

437
00:30:55,416 --> 00:30:59,915
♪Do your best and don't let go♪

438
00:31:02,641 --> 00:31:08,251
♪You said those moments
from the past burned us both♪

439
00:31:09,688 --> 00:31:15,258
♪Though the story found no end,
and the promise broke♪

440
00:31:16,629 --> 00:31:22,999
♪That so-called happiness
became pain without a place to land♪

441
00:31:22,999 --> 00:31:29,051
♪All the rights and wrongs
will fade away♪

442
00:31:30,872 --> 00:31:37,560
♪I really want to know
where you landed later♪

443
00:31:37,944 --> 00:31:44,536
♪So many words I've wanted to say,
yet I find myself speechless♪

444
00:31:48,332 --> 00:31:49,052
It's not right.

445
00:31:49,933 --> 00:31:51,292
Yumo's expression isn't like this.

446
00:31:51,292 --> 00:31:57,280
♪Make a wish upon a shooting star,
may it come true♪

447
00:31:57,280 --> 00:32:04,366
♪Maybe a scar hides deep in your heart♪

448
00:32:04,366 --> 00:32:10,968
♪Hope someone comes to make it right♪

449
00:32:10,968 --> 00:32:15,096
♪Walking with you, making flowers bloom♪

450
00:32:15,096 --> 00:32:19,416
♪Can you feel me this way♪

451
00:32:19,416 --> 00:32:25,720
♪Even in dreams, I'm saying, be happy♪

452
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:32,806
♪Perhaps I still can't let go
in my heart♪

453
00:32:32,806 --> 00:32:39,224
♪Time never lingers for love's sake♪

454
00:32:39,224 --> 00:32:43,443
♪But the world's complexity won't break♪

455
00:32:43,443 --> 00:32:48,871
♪I pray love's course remains true♪

456
00:32:51,288 --> 00:32:56,589
♪Wherever you are,
may happiness find you♪

457
00:32:57,560 --> 00:32:59,798
♪Remember this♪

458
00:33:09,784 --> 00:33:11,653
Here, try this.

459
00:33:12,532 --> 00:33:13,812
I just made these.

460
00:33:15,252 --> 00:33:17,492
When the knife cuts in,
the oil sizzles out.

461
00:33:17,492 --> 00:33:18,213
Yeah.

462
00:33:27,332 --> 00:33:28,332
Tastes pretty good.

463
00:33:28,492 --> 00:33:30,092
It's alright, I guess.

464
00:33:30,973 --> 00:33:31,812
You know what?

465
00:33:31,812 --> 00:33:35,012
If we wait a few more days
for the saltiness to soak in,

466
00:33:35,052 --> 00:33:37,332
- the flavor'll be amazing, I swear.
- Indeed.

467
00:33:37,332 --> 00:33:39,332
A bit bland. Just slightly undersalted.

468
00:33:39,812 --> 00:33:40,613
Not bad.

469
00:33:40,893 --> 00:33:41,893
Go ahead and eat.

470
00:33:42,173 --> 00:33:43,012
No.

471
00:33:45,693 --> 00:33:46,492
Well?

472
00:33:46,732 --> 00:33:48,453
How's your dad's health lately?

473
00:33:50,012 --> 00:33:52,613
His health's about the same.

474
00:33:53,252 --> 00:33:55,373
If you face any difficulties,
just tell us.

475
00:33:58,252 --> 00:33:59,772
The nurse mentioned to me

476
00:34:00,772 --> 00:34:05,613
that your wife often brings my dad
homemade food.

477
00:34:07,532 --> 00:34:08,333
Thanks.

478
00:34:08,813 --> 00:34:10,612
No need to be polite with me.

479
00:34:11,132 --> 00:34:13,212
An elder at home is like a treasure.

480
00:34:13,612 --> 00:34:16,293
We should take good care
of such a treasure.

481
00:34:16,293 --> 00:34:16,933
Don't you agree?

482
00:34:16,933 --> 00:34:17,572
Yes.

483
00:34:17,853 --> 00:34:18,973
It's our blessing.

484
00:34:21,853 --> 00:34:22,933
Alright, you eat.

485
00:34:23,212 --> 00:34:24,012
I'm back to work.

486
00:34:24,012 --> 00:34:24,532
Okay.

487
00:34:39,373 --> 00:34:41,492
Ten, eleven.

488
00:34:41,492 --> 00:34:42,893
Why suddenly use this?

489
00:34:42,893 --> 00:34:43,652
Twelve.

490
00:34:44,492 --> 00:34:45,413
To exercise.

491
00:34:46,933 --> 00:34:48,373
I never see you work out normally.

492
00:34:50,012 --> 00:34:51,893
Well, nobody runs with me anymore.

493
00:34:54,492 --> 00:34:55,973
You need company to run?

494
00:34:57,933 --> 00:34:59,012
I'm serious.

495
00:34:59,492 --> 00:35:00,532
You've moved out,

496
00:35:00,532 --> 00:35:01,813
and I get really bored alone.

497
00:35:02,092 --> 00:35:04,333
That's why I came early
to exercise at the office.

498
00:35:20,853 --> 00:35:21,773
Get to the point.

499
00:35:23,692 --> 00:35:24,853
Forget it, never mind.

500
00:35:25,413 --> 00:35:27,172
You can't talk about your girlfriend

501
00:35:27,212 --> 00:35:28,692
or your confidential mission.

502
00:35:29,092 --> 00:35:31,973
Living like this every day
must exhaust you.

503
00:35:35,132 --> 00:35:37,333
Honestly, I envy you sometimes.

504
00:35:38,652 --> 00:35:41,692
I wish I could be unburdened like you

505
00:35:41,813 --> 00:35:43,092
and live lightly and openly,

506
00:35:43,773 --> 00:35:44,973
so carefree.

507
00:35:47,012 --> 00:35:48,293
Actually, sometimes

508
00:35:49,652 --> 00:35:51,492
it's just a split-second decision.

509
00:35:51,572 --> 00:35:54,813
Once you figure it out,
you can live freely.

510
00:35:57,132 --> 00:35:59,092
That was unexpectedly profound.

511
00:35:59,453 --> 00:36:01,572
Of course, I mean it sincerely.

512
00:36:06,212 --> 00:36:07,532
Hope that day comes.

513
00:36:08,253 --> 00:36:09,492
It definitely will come.

514
00:36:09,492 --> 00:36:11,492
I'll always be here
when you need me, bro.

515
00:36:11,733 --> 00:36:13,893
Just don't stick around
when I don't need you.

516
00:36:14,853 --> 00:36:15,492
Bye.

517
00:36:19,160 --> 00:36:31,288
(Rose Garden Hotel)

518
00:37:14,172 --> 00:37:15,612
The victim is Mai Qianqian.

519
00:37:15,612 --> 00:37:17,532
Female, 49 years old, from Yushan.

520
00:37:17,853 --> 00:37:19,293
She checked in yesterday afternoon.

521
00:37:19,572 --> 00:37:22,333
The preliminary COD
is blunt force head trauma.

522
00:37:24,652 --> 00:37:29,532
Time of death
was around 2 to 3 AM last night.

523
00:37:30,052 --> 00:37:32,413
This matches
what the neighboring guest reported.

524
00:37:33,052 --> 00:37:34,132
The neighboring guest

525
00:37:34,132 --> 00:37:38,012
said they heard arguing and fighting
in Room 601 last night.

526
00:37:38,492 --> 00:37:40,492
So they complained to the front desk.

527
00:37:41,132 --> 00:37:44,092
The front desk
then called Room 601 to check.

528
00:37:44,293 --> 00:37:45,813
But a man answered the phone,

529
00:37:46,172 --> 00:37:47,893
claiming it's a couple's fight.

530
00:37:48,132 --> 00:37:49,413
Then all noise stopped.

531
00:37:50,052 --> 00:37:52,492
Housekeeping came to clean this morning.

532
00:37:52,492 --> 00:37:54,532
Only then did they find
the victim was dead.

533
00:37:56,813 --> 00:37:58,692
There are signs of a struggle
at the scene.

534
00:37:59,293 --> 00:38:01,212
Based on the size of these wounds,

535
00:38:01,532 --> 00:38:05,373
the ashtray is most likely
the murder weapon.

536
00:38:06,492 --> 00:38:08,652
But hotels by the train station

537
00:38:08,652 --> 00:38:09,773
are all about traffic.

538
00:38:10,132 --> 00:38:12,092
The cleaning is basically just for show.

539
00:38:13,012 --> 00:38:14,413
Could be multiple sets of prints.

540
00:38:16,973 --> 00:38:19,453
But if the suspect
answered the phone call,

541
00:38:21,612 --> 00:38:22,973
it should have his fingerprints.

542
00:38:23,413 --> 00:38:24,773
We might even extract DNA.

543
00:38:24,853 --> 00:38:26,612
This hotel is quite irresponsible.

544
00:38:27,253 --> 00:38:31,012
Why didn't they come up to check
when there was arguing and fighting?

545
00:38:31,532 --> 00:38:33,293
For fighting in the middle of the night,

546
00:38:34,092 --> 00:38:35,773
if it's strangers, that's one thing.

547
00:38:35,773 --> 00:38:36,773
But if it's a couple,

548
00:38:36,773 --> 00:38:38,373
people might not want to get involved.

549
00:38:38,373 --> 00:38:41,333
Even the local police
avoid such trouble.

550
00:38:41,733 --> 00:38:43,652
Often, you arrest the man,

551
00:38:43,652 --> 00:38:46,052
and the woman shows up
demanding his release.

552
00:38:46,052 --> 00:38:46,973
It's not worth it.

553
00:38:47,692 --> 00:38:48,492
Ziwu,

554
00:38:48,773 --> 00:38:50,492
what's that under the victim's neck?

555
00:38:59,572 --> 00:39:00,413
A blood clot.

556
00:39:04,052 --> 00:39:07,532
The suspect likely
struck the victim's head twice.

557
00:39:07,773 --> 00:39:10,692
The first blow
didn't cause immediate death.

558
00:39:12,052 --> 00:39:14,813
There was likely a time gap
between the two blows.

559
00:39:16,212 --> 00:39:17,893
The interval was about...

560
00:39:20,172 --> 00:39:21,132
twenty minutes.

561
00:39:21,853 --> 00:39:24,373
Twenty minutes
is enough time to do a lot.

562
00:39:25,333 --> 00:39:27,933
The victim's ID and documents
were still in her bag.

563
00:39:27,933 --> 00:39:28,933
And bank cards too.

564
00:39:28,973 --> 00:39:30,092
Plus a fair amount of cash.

565
00:39:32,973 --> 00:39:34,293
The victim's clothes were intact.

566
00:39:35,132 --> 00:39:36,492
No signs of sexual assault.

567
00:39:37,813 --> 00:39:38,853
Hard to say.

568
00:39:39,012 --> 00:39:42,532
The hotel front desk
registered her with no companion.

569
00:39:43,052 --> 00:39:45,413
But the hotel can't stop guests
from bringing people in.

570
00:39:46,212 --> 00:39:49,813
We currently can't ID the man
who answered the phone call.

571
00:39:50,132 --> 00:39:53,012
We've requested
the hotel's surveillance footage.

572
00:39:53,652 --> 00:39:55,893
But this building is very old.

573
00:39:56,012 --> 00:39:59,453
Cameras are only in the lobby,
front door, and elevators on each floor.

574
00:39:59,453 --> 00:40:01,293
So the investigation
faces some difficulty.

575
00:40:01,733 --> 00:40:02,572
Also,

576
00:40:03,212 --> 00:40:05,453
the victim's phone is missing.

577
00:40:05,532 --> 00:40:07,333
It might have been taken by the suspect.

578
00:40:07,893 --> 00:40:11,293
I'm collecting biological evidence
from under the victim's fingernails.

579
00:40:12,733 --> 00:40:16,293
Since they fought,
we should find the suspect's tissue.

580
00:41:46,973 --> 00:41:47,572
Long.

581
00:41:47,572 --> 00:41:48,293
Ziwu.

582
00:41:48,293 --> 00:41:50,172
Did you verify
the victim's fingerprints?

583
00:41:51,132 --> 00:41:53,413
By testing the victim's blood sample,

584
00:41:53,572 --> 00:41:55,612
DNA shows she had a criminal record

585
00:41:56,172 --> 00:41:58,692
and was a fugitive wanted by the police.

586
00:41:58,813 --> 00:42:00,092
The victim?

587
00:42:01,973 --> 00:42:03,492
On my end,

588
00:42:04,172 --> 00:42:07,092
(Liu Jianyuan's Info)
fingerprints from the ashtray and phone

589
00:42:07,092 --> 00:42:07,893
are in the system.

590
00:42:07,893 --> 00:42:09,893
But that's a man named Liu Jianyuan.

591
00:42:10,572 --> 00:42:11,733
Back in 2011,

592
00:42:11,733 --> 00:42:15,132
for robbery and assault, he was
sentenced to six years, eight months.

593
00:42:15,132 --> 00:42:16,853
He's now a fugitive.

594
00:42:17,172 --> 00:42:21,492
A woman named Liu Min
was his accomplice.

595
00:42:21,853 --> 00:42:22,652
Liu Min?

596
00:42:24,333 --> 00:42:26,773
The victim's DNA confirms
she is Liu Min.

597
00:42:28,572 --> 00:42:32,692
So the ID used at the hotel
was either fake or stolen.

598
00:42:34,652 --> 00:42:38,132
Is Liu Jianyuan's DNA
among the evidence from the scene?

599
00:42:38,413 --> 00:42:39,853
If it is...

600
00:42:39,853 --> 00:42:42,733
The test results
from the fingernail scrapings are in.

601
00:42:43,052 --> 00:42:43,973
It's Liu Jianyuan.

602
00:42:47,248 --> 00:42:50,741
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

603
00:42:54,535 --> 00:42:59,856
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

604
00:43:01,929 --> 00:43:06,783
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

605
00:43:07,589 --> 00:43:10,736
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

606
00:43:10,736 --> 00:43:13,840
♪To shield us from the storm♪

607
00:43:16,496 --> 00:43:21,630
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

608
00:43:23,600 --> 00:43:29,232
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

609
00:43:30,992 --> 00:43:34,576
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

610
00:43:35,728 --> 00:43:43,168
♪Converging into your form♪

611
00:43:43,600 --> 00:43:46,278
♪Looking up♪

612
00:43:46,278 --> 00:43:49,817
♪Such dazzling glory♪

613
00:43:50,800 --> 00:43:53,360
♪Like hope♪

614
00:43:53,360 --> 00:43:57,293
♪Reaching out its arms♪

615
00:43:58,160 --> 00:44:00,812
♪Cloaked in light♪

616
00:44:00,812 --> 00:44:05,296
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

617
00:44:05,296 --> 00:44:08,112
♪Traversing♪

618
00:44:08,112 --> 00:44:14,623
♪The battlefield of fate♪
